  "prob_desc_output_spec": "If it's impossible to find the representation of n as a product of k numbers, print -1. Otherwise, print k integers in any order. Their product must be equal to n. If there are multiple answers, print any of them.",
  "source_code": "#include<stdio.h>\nint main(int argc, char const *argv[])\n{\n  int n,k,count=0,i=2;\n  scanf(\"%d %d\",&n,&k);\n  int arr[k];\n  while(count!=k-1 && n>1)\n  {\n    if(n%i==0)\n    {\n      n=n/i;\n      arr[count]=i;\n      count++;\n      i=2;\n    }\n    else i++;\n     \n  }\n  if(n<=1 && count!=k)\n  printf(\"-1\");\n  else\n  {\n  arr[count]=n;\n  for(i=0;i<k;i++)\n  printf(\"%d \",arr[i]);\n  return 0;\n  }\n}\n",
